    "text": "Q4. A solution of \\(Na_2CO_3\\) has a strength of \\(10.6\\,g\\,L^{-1}\\).\n(Molar mass of \\(Na_2CO_3 = 106\\,g\\,mol^{-1}\\))\nCalculate the normality of the solution.",
    "image": null
  },
  "options": [
    { "id": "a", "text": "0.05 N" },
    { "id": "b", "text": "0.10 N" },
    { "id": "c", "text": "0.20 N" },
    { "id": "d", "text": "0.50 N" }
  ],
  "correct_answer": "c",
  "solution": {
    "text": "\\[N = \\frac{\\text{Strength}}{\\text{Equivalent weight}}\\]",
    "image": null
  },
  "solution_steps": [
    "Step 1: Write formula",
    "\\[N = \\frac{\\text{Weight per litre}}{\\text{Equivalent weight}}\\]",

    "Step 2: Determine n-factor",
    "\\[CO_3^{2-} + 2H^+ \\rightarrow H_2CO_3\\]",
    "Thus, \\(n = 2\\)",

    "Step 3: Calculate equivalent weight",
    "\\[\\text{Equivalent weight} = \\frac{106}{2} = 53\\]",

    "Step 4: Substitute values",
    "\\[N = \\frac{10.6}{53}\\]",

    "Step 5: Solve",
    "\\[N = 0.20\\]",

    "Final Answer: 0.20 N"
  ]
